snippet.textDisplay:
I like the Alyx character, but find it kind of bullshitty that Episode 3 and/or Half-Life 3 was "too big of a project to work on". I don't buy that for a second.

They're releasing a video game with a female main character to stay in business because that's one of the new trends. Making everything about women and acting like every man on the planet is just the worst. At least this is a prequel to Half-Life 2, meaning that Doctor Freeman has yet to rise and shine.

Although, there is Portal, and I LOVE PORTAL! Female player character, female villain. And then Wheatley, who's just the worst. But it's not because they needed to sell their game, it's because they wanted a plot twist.

Everything in this day and age with a female lead just makes me weary that it exists to exist. There are plenty of exceptions, though. I think.
